WEBVTT

00:08.597 --> 00:11.237
That body you found yesterday.
It's Tommy Lee Royce's mother.

00:13.224 --> 00:15.863
You're not exactly a barrel
of laughs yourself, you know, kid.

00:15.864 --> 00:18.583
I'm going to a funeral
this afternoon. So is my granny!

00:18.584 --> 00:20.943
You killed my mother,
you filthy bitch!

00:20.944 --> 00:22.983
You're going to get
what's coming to you!

00:22.984 --> 00:25.063
Was it sudden? Cancer.

00:25.064 --> 00:27.823
They're accusing me of strangling
and bottling Lynn Dewhurst.

00:27.824 --> 00:29.103
I'm sorry.

00:29.104 --> 00:30.743
I am sorry.

00:30.744 --> 00:33.223
I'll be fine.
Tomorrow, I'll start again.

00:33.224 --> 00:37.104
No, tomorrow, you'll need another
drink. If you... Will you shift?

00:39.000 --> 00:45.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:46.184 --> 00:48.663
I saw on the sheet
that I asked you to fill in...

00:48.664 --> 00:50.224
Oh, the happy sheet?

00:51.864 --> 00:54.264
Yes, the happy sheet.

00:55.664 --> 00:57.623
I saw that on the question -

00:57.624 --> 01:00.423
have you ever contemplated
killing yourself or others? -

01:00.424 --> 01:01.904
you've written "yes".

01:03.784 --> 01:06.383
Do you want to talk about that? No.

01:06.384 --> 01:09.063
Have you ever contemplated
killing yourself?

01:09.064 --> 01:11.623
Have you ever TRIED
to kill yourself? No.

01:11.624 --> 01:14.103
Have you ever thought about
how you might do it if you did?

01:14.104 --> 01:16.943
I've seen all of 'em
and none of 'em are pretty.

01:16.944 --> 01:20.504
They're all...
All what? Sordid. Ridiculous.

01:21.984 --> 01:24.383
And, anyway,
I don't want to be on a slab.

01:24.384 --> 01:26.264
I've seen what they do to people.

01:27.864 --> 01:31.103
Did you have counselling after
your daughter took her own life?

01:31.104 --> 01:32.584
No, I had a breakdown.

01:33.984 --> 01:37.063
What happened? Nothing. I just...

01:37.064 --> 01:39.983
screamed at people a lot
and smashed a few things in the sink

01:39.984 --> 01:41.744
and drank too much and...

01:42.824 --> 01:45.303
...pissed everyone off
within a ten-mile radius

01:45.304 --> 01:47.623
for about a year, 18 months,
and then...

01:47.624 --> 01:49.104
you know?

01:50.864 --> 01:54.423
You've still got to pay the mortgage
at the end of it all, haven't you?

01:54.424 --> 01:57.903
And your marriage broke down.
Well, yeah.

01:57.904 --> 02:01.343
Most marriages don't survive
something like that, do they?

02:01.344 --> 02:02.863
Losing a child.

02:02.864 --> 02:06.104
An experience like that
changes people. Permanently.

02:07.624 --> 02:09.144
I'd have said so.

02:10.383 --> 02:12.064
How did it change you?

02:13.344 --> 02:14.904
I'm sad.

02:18.424 --> 02:21.463
I never used to be sad.
I mean, I could be sad. But...

02:21.464 --> 02:24.024
it wasn't like it was
a permanent state of...

02:29.624 --> 02:31.623
It didn't define who I am.

02:31.624 --> 02:34.783
You don't appear sad. I'm sorry,
I don't mean to contradict

02:34.784 --> 02:37.743
the fact that you are sad.
Only you know how you feel.

02:37.744 --> 02:40.263
But your colleagues,
your friends at work,

02:40.264 --> 02:43.903
I get the idea that they see you
as the life and soul of the party.

02:43.904 --> 02:45.743
Good.

02:45.744 --> 02:47.624
Do you cover things up? No.

02:49.144 --> 02:51.663
No, they all know about Becky,
they all know what happened.

02:51.664 --> 02:53.663
No, I mean do you...

02:53.664 --> 02:55.943
Are you conscious of feeling sad

02:55.944 --> 02:59.463
but still trying to put on a brave
face, your happy face, at work?

02:59.464 --> 03:01.144
No, I love work.

03:03.104 --> 03:04.703
Do you think you're angry?

03:04.704 --> 03:06.224
As well as sad?

03:07.304 --> 03:08.784
Sometimes.

03:09.784 --> 03:11.423
You have an edge.

03:11.424 --> 03:14.583
People are a bit scared of you,
aren't they? Who said that?

03:14.584 --> 03:16.103
It's an observation.

03:16.104 --> 03:20.383
How do you feel about that,
people being scared of you?

03:20.384 --> 03:24.223
Well, it's useful occasionally, if
I'm dealing with something at work.

03:24.224 --> 03:27.223
I often have to deal with people
who are a lot bigger than me.

03:27.224 --> 03:29.904
Are you scared of me? Should I be?
No. No.

03:31.184 --> 03:32.623
Nobody needs to be scared of me

03:32.624 --> 03:35.743
unless they've done something
they shouldn't have.

03:35.744 --> 03:38.583
The second part of that question -
"others".

03:38.584 --> 03:41.623
Have you ever
contemplated killing others?

03:41.624 --> 03:43.743
Does the "yes" apply there?

03:43.744 --> 03:45.583
Oh, yeah.

03:45.584 --> 03:47.064
Tell me about that.

03:50.064 --> 03:53.423
When was the last time
that you felt like that?

03:53.424 --> 03:55.663
Well, day before yesterday,

03:55.664 --> 03:57.703
I could've merrily
strung my grandson up

03:57.704 --> 04:00.103
for setting off a fire extinguisher
at school

04:00.104 --> 04:03.023
because someone bet him
a bag of crisps he couldn't.

04:03.024 --> 04:05.783
So that's me hauled in
and being made to feel this big.

04:05.784 --> 04:07.743
Again.

04:07.744 --> 04:11.103
Then, last Thursday, I could've
happily throttled my son,

04:11.104 --> 04:13.623
who, after persistently
denying anything,

04:13.624 --> 04:15.183
finally admitted he'd had a fling

04:15.184 --> 04:17.343
with his nasty little bitch
of an ex-girlfriend

04:17.344 --> 04:19.623
whilst his perfectly lovely wife
was in hospital

04:19.624 --> 04:21.822
giving birth
to their first child.

04:21.824 --> 04:23.503
So he's a liar.

04:23.504 --> 04:24.984
And then... When was it?

04:26.544 --> 04:27.904
Two weeks ago?

04:29.464 --> 04:32.344
I could've cheerfully
strangled my sister Clare.

04:34.184 --> 04:35.744
She's an alcoholic.

04:37.024 --> 04:40.343
A recovering alcoholic
and heroin addict.

04:40.344 --> 04:42.263
She's been dry and clean -

04:42.264 --> 04:45.863
apart from one or two blips
with alcohol - for nearly 12 years.

04:45.864 --> 04:48.743
Then she fell off the wagon
at this funeral.

04:48.744 --> 04:50.664
And said it was my fault, which...

04:52.344 --> 04:54.543
...it was and it wasn't.

04:54.544 --> 04:57.303
In fact, that was the same day
that I did this thing

04:57.304 --> 05:01.104
that's meant I'm having to do
this business here... with you.

05:03.064 --> 05:04.943
Trouble Town by Jake Bugg

05:04.944 --> 05:07.343
♪ There's a tower block overhead

05:07.344 --> 05:09.263
♪ All you've got's your benefits

05:09.264 --> 05:11.824
♪ And you're barely scraping by

05:14.424 --> 05:17.263
♪ In this trouble town

05:17.264 --> 05:20.624
♪ Troubles are found

05:25.624 --> 05:27.383
♪ Stuck in speed bump city

05:27.384 --> 05:29.663
♪ Where the only thing that's pretty

05:29.664 --> 05:31.904
♪ Is the thought of getting out. ♪

05:35.904 --> 05:38.903
Tell me about Clare. Two weeks ago.

05:38.904 --> 05:42.503
Why did she think it was your fault
that she'd fallen off the wagon?

05:42.504 --> 05:44.823
I thought you were stopping!

05:44.824 --> 05:49.383
I thought we were both stopping,
and then suddenly you're not!

05:49.384 --> 05:54.223
And I'm there on me own,
and I don't know anybody,

05:54.224 --> 05:57.063
except for, like, three people.

05:57.064 --> 05:59.584
And you were five hours!

06:00.624 --> 06:04.943
You said, "I shan't be so long,"
or whatever.

06:04.944 --> 06:08.183
There's no buses up there,
where they live.

06:08.184 --> 06:10.183
Well...

06:10.184 --> 06:13.103
there are might be,
but I don't know where they go.

06:13.104 --> 06:15.983
So what am I supposed to do?

06:15.984 --> 06:18.263
Walk home? Hitch a lift?

06:18.264 --> 06:20.183
Call a... taxi?

06:20.184 --> 06:21.824
Fly?! Clare?

06:23.424 --> 06:25.783
Well, if it isn't our Clare!

06:25.784 --> 06:28.423
How's yerself?
Where you been, eh?

06:28.424 --> 06:30.263
I've not seen you for years.

06:30.264 --> 06:32.063
Spike. Ahh!

06:32.064 --> 06:33.863
Eh, am I interrupting?

06:33.864 --> 06:35.543
No, we were, um...

06:35.544 --> 06:38.383
I'm not interrupting.
Only, I just saw you

06:38.384 --> 06:40.863
and I thought I'd say hello, cos...

06:40.864 --> 06:42.584
Bloody 'ell!

06:45.984 --> 06:47.383
Do I know you?

06:47.384 --> 06:48.823
You look familiar.

06:48.824 --> 06:50.463
It's me sister.

06:50.464 --> 06:52.743
Ah, that's it! That'll be it.

06:52.744 --> 06:54.383
Catherine.

06:54.384 --> 06:55.984
Spike. How do you do?

06:57.184 --> 07:00.423
I thought I knew you.
I thought you were...

07:00.424 --> 07:03.823
There's this copper round 'ere,
she has a look o' you.

07:03.824 --> 07:07.463
She's a right bitch -
pardon my French.

07:07.464 --> 07:09.583
She thinks she's well 'ard.

07:09.584 --> 07:12.263
She did our Aaron for possession,
right?

07:12.264 --> 07:15.223
Nearly broke his bloody arm.

07:15.224 --> 07:17.304
Not you, obviously.

07:18.784 --> 07:21.383
Yeah, well,
happen if he'd gone quietly,

07:21.384 --> 07:24.424
she wouldn't have needed
to show him who's in charge.

07:34.184 --> 07:38.104
It was Tommy Lee Royce's mother's
funeral an hour after Helen's.

07:39.184 --> 07:40.343
Same crematorium.

07:40.344 --> 07:43.023
That's why I left - I went back.
I'm sorry.

07:43.024 --> 07:45.383
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have left you.

07:45.384 --> 07:47.903
I knew you were vulnerable
and I shouldn't have gone,

07:47.904 --> 07:49.743
but that's why. So...

07:49.744 --> 07:51.304
I'm sorry.

07:52.984 --> 07:54.224
You're joking.

07:56.344 --> 07:59.424
You could have said.
That I would've understood.

08:01.664 --> 08:04.463
Was he there?
Did they let him out of prison?

08:04.464 --> 08:06.304
Yeah.

08:08.104 --> 08:09.584
Wow...

09:05.384 --> 09:08.223
Daniel? Daniel?

09:08.224 --> 09:09.504
Daniel?

09:10.984 --> 09:13.463
Sorry. Can you do me a favour, love?

09:13.464 --> 09:15.863
Can you get Ryan
off to school on time?

09:15.864 --> 09:18.023
I've got to get off to work
and Clare's...

09:18.024 --> 09:20.063
She all right? Oh, God knows.

09:20.064 --> 09:23.623
Either way, I can't see her
surfacing much before dinner time.

09:23.624 --> 09:25.863
I'm sorry to ask.
I wouldn't have...

09:25.864 --> 09:27.463
Oh, it's fine, don't worry.

09:27.464 --> 09:29.663
I'll drop him off on my way to work.

09:29.664 --> 09:31.263
Tea. Thanks.

09:31.264 --> 09:33.544
I love you. Mm.

09:38.104 --> 09:40.744
I wish I knew what was going on
with you.

09:42.464 --> 09:45.543
Will you make sure
he gets some breakfast inside him?

09:45.544 --> 09:46.824
Course.

09:53.984 --> 09:57.064
Last but not least,
there was a...

09:58.064 --> 10:00.783
...house fire in a flat
above a shop in Ripponden

10:00.784 --> 10:03.223
reported just after midnight
this morning.

10:03.224 --> 10:04.863
The flat was burnt out, apparently.

10:04.864 --> 10:07.463
The fire officer is telling us
there are several indicators

10:07.464 --> 10:09.103
pointing towards arson, OK?

10:09.104 --> 10:11.943
There was no-one in the flat,
so we're looking for the tenant,

10:11.944 --> 10:14.863
who is a Vicky - Victoria -
Vicky Fleming.

10:14.864 --> 10:16.703
50 years old.

10:16.704 --> 10:20.463
She works on the make-up counter
at Oswald Department Store,

10:20.464 --> 10:22.983
according to the landlord
who owns the shop.

10:22.984 --> 10:25.983
So, Shaf, can you go and see
if she's in work this morning

10:25.984 --> 10:28.143
and what she knows
about what's happened?

10:28.144 --> 10:31.823
Ann, will you go with him?
Right. That's all, folks.

10:31.824 --> 10:33.783
Mind how you go.

10:33.784 --> 10:35.824
Morning, sir. Morning, boss.

10:43.304 --> 10:45.503
Chief Super's coming in to see you.

10:45.504 --> 10:48.744
1.30 this aft.
It'll be in my office.

10:50.744 --> 10:52.344
Pillock.

10:54.224 --> 10:55.704
You all right?

11:00.584 --> 11:02.663
Have you thought about retirement?

11:02.664 --> 11:03.983
No, sir.

11:03.984 --> 11:05.143
Medical retirement.

11:05.144 --> 11:06.864
Why? What's wrong with me?

11:08.464 --> 11:10.704
18 months ago, you nearly died.

11:11.984 --> 11:15.663
My wrist aches when the temperature
drops below zero,

11:15.664 --> 11:18.424
but other than that...

11:20.664 --> 11:22.863
A thing like that takes its toll

11:22.864 --> 11:25.463
mentally as well as physically,
Catherine.

11:25.464 --> 11:28.583
We did go some way down the medical
retirement route last time.

11:28.584 --> 11:32.423
Yeah, and it weren't what I wanted
then, and it isn't what I want now.

11:32.424 --> 11:33.744
Sir.

11:36.624 --> 11:40.423
It would appear to me
that you have unresolved issues,

11:40.424 --> 11:43.143
which is why you turned up
at that funeral yesterday -

11:43.144 --> 11:46.263
a funeral which you and me
both know, for 1,001 reasons,

11:46.264 --> 11:48.704
you shouldn't have been
anywhere near.

11:50.104 --> 11:53.944
You were offered counselling when
you left hospital 18 months ago.

11:55.464 --> 11:57.103
Yeah. Did you go?

11:57.104 --> 11:58.383
Yeah.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.984
Did you complete
the course of treatment?

12:04.424 --> 12:08.503
OK. I'm giving you options,
Catherine. Two options.

12:08.504 --> 12:10.663
I'd like you to see
the force psychologist.

12:10.664 --> 12:11.743
I'd like you to complete

12:11.744 --> 12:14.023
whatever course of treatment
he suggests to you.

12:14.024 --> 12:15.623
Or the alternative -

12:15.624 --> 12:19.103
and I do think it's something
you should consider...

12:19.104 --> 12:21.823
Seriously, you've had a long
and distinguished career,

12:21.824 --> 12:24.983
you're a highly respected officer
who's suffered a major trauma.

12:24.984 --> 12:27.743
Why don't I have a case conference
with HR to take things forward

12:27.744 --> 12:30.463
down the medical retirement route?
You're not doing that to me.

12:30.464 --> 12:32.663
There is no stigma attached.
You'd...

12:32.664 --> 12:34.583
You'd retire on a full pension...

12:34.584 --> 12:37.103
Yeah, and I'd miss
the next three years' salary.

12:37.104 --> 12:39.424
Well, do you want to think about it?
No.

12:40.784 --> 12:43.224
Fine.
So you'll take the first option.

12:44.824 --> 12:47.663
You'll see the force psychologist,
you'll remain operational,

12:47.664 --> 12:49.583
but, this time, you will complete

12:49.584 --> 12:52.424
whatever course of treatment
he suggests to you.

12:56.144 --> 12:59.864
And has Clare managed to stay dry
during the last two weeks?

13:01.984 --> 13:04.503
It's early days. But, er...

13:04.504 --> 13:07.863
yeah. It was a lapse,
it shook her more than anyone.

13:07.864 --> 13:10.823
She's been at
every AA meeting going since.

13:10.824 --> 13:13.544
They do all sorts -
they have a jive class...

13:15.584 --> 13:17.704
She goes with this new boyfriend.

13:18.984 --> 13:21.503
What about Daniel?

13:21.504 --> 13:23.103
God knows.

13:23.104 --> 13:24.824
And Ryan?

13:26.144 --> 13:28.703
Well, he can be fine for weeks.
But...

13:28.704 --> 13:31.303
you never know
when the phone's going to go,

13:31.304 --> 13:32.703
and it'll be Mrs Beresford -

13:32.704 --> 13:35.703
"You're going to have to come in
and fetch him." So...

13:35.704 --> 13:37.303
You have a lot on.

13:37.304 --> 13:40.423
Ah, no more than most people my age,
I suspect.

13:40.424 --> 13:43.863
You did something very selfless
when you took Ryan on.

13:43.864 --> 13:46.743
There must have been times
when you've struggled with it.

13:46.744 --> 13:48.183
Well, I don't dwell on it.

13:48.184 --> 13:51.144
I've always focused on the fact
that it isn't his fault.

13:53.584 --> 13:55.944
Tell me about Tommy Lee Royce.

13:58.744 --> 14:00.503
What about him?

14:00.504 --> 14:02.504
What took you to the funeral?

14:11.664 --> 14:14.823
I have a friend
who's scared of birds.

14:14.824 --> 14:16.463
It's a proper phobia.

14:16.464 --> 14:19.024
And, um, one day, this peacock...

14:20.064 --> 14:22.943
...came and sat just outside
her front door.

14:22.944 --> 14:26.543
I've no idea where it came from,
but it just sat there for hours.

14:26.544 --> 14:29.463
And she didn't dare go out,
and her husband was at work,

14:29.464 --> 14:31.903
and she said she felt
too stupid to ring anyone.

14:31.904 --> 14:35.983
So she just stared at it through
the sitting room window for hours

14:35.984 --> 14:37.823
till it left,

14:37.824 --> 14:39.504
and I said, "Why?"

14:40.864 --> 14:43.064
And she said,
"So I knew where it was."

14:44.744 --> 14:47.383
So maybe that's it,
maybe that's all it was.

14:47.384 --> 14:48.744
I just...

14:50.704 --> 14:54.344
...wanted to make sure I knew where
he was till he was back inside.

14:57.304 --> 14:59.224
Going back to the question...

15:00.504 --> 15:03.863
...have you ever contemplated
killing yourself or others?

15:03.864 --> 15:06.704
What about him, Tommy Lee Royce?

15:08.464 --> 15:11.223
My daughter died because of him.
What do you think?

15:11.224 --> 15:13.024
Tell me about that. Look...

15:16.584 --> 15:18.423
...if I'd really wanted to kill him,

15:18.424 --> 15:21.263
I could've done on that narrow boat,
18 months since.

15:21.264 --> 15:23.143
I had him on the floor,
he was helpless,

15:23.144 --> 15:25.543
I could have kicked the stuffing out
of him, but I didn't.

15:25.544 --> 15:27.423
What I actually did
was douse him in foam

15:27.424 --> 15:29.063
so he couldn't set fire to himself.

15:29.064 --> 15:30.943
When it came to it,
when the chips were down,

15:30.944 --> 15:32.863
my instinct
was to do the right thing.

15:32.864 --> 15:35.824
And do you regret that? No.

15:38.104 --> 15:39.584
How was it?

15:41.024 --> 15:42.303
That bad?

15:42.304 --> 15:44.423
You just hear yourself talking wank.

15:44.424 --> 15:47.503
Dripping off the ceiling
and crawling down the walls.

15:47.504 --> 15:49.743
The room's so full of it
by the time you've finished,

15:49.744 --> 15:52.303
you've to wade through it
in your wellies to get out.

15:52.304 --> 15:53.823
Do you fancy a drink tonight?

15:53.824 --> 15:56.144
You fancy going out
for something to eat?

15:58.784 --> 16:00.543
Yeah, actually. That'd be nice.

16:00.544 --> 16:02.343
My treat. Why?

16:02.344 --> 16:05.023
Cos I feel like chucking
me brass about. Ooh...

16:05.024 --> 16:06.903
OK.

16:06.904 --> 16:08.584
And in other news... What?

16:10.304 --> 16:13.263
...they think they've found
another body.

16:13.264 --> 16:16.984
Where? Going over to Brighouse
again. Same as first one.

16:32.024 --> 16:35.863
There's been nothing found
at the scene to identify who she is.

16:35.864 --> 16:38.503
What we know at the moment is
she's white,

16:38.504 --> 16:40.823
she's 5ft 4in, slight build.

16:40.824 --> 16:43.263
She's got blonde,
shoulder-length hair.

16:43.264 --> 16:46.783
Shoe size - 5.
She's between 30 and 60 years old.

16:46.784 --> 16:49.943
So we need to check all the mispers
locally, force wide,

16:49.944 --> 16:51.863
and then moving out force by force,

16:51.864 --> 16:55.063
going back, I'd say...
four weeks, initially.

16:55.064 --> 16:56.543
CCTV in the area -

16:56.544 --> 17:00.103
may be limited, but
I'd like to see what we can gather.

17:00.104 --> 17:02.703
As you go in,
it says the site's covered,

17:02.704 --> 17:04.623
but I didn't see any cameras.

17:04.624 --> 17:07.424
Again, I'd say going back
four weeks.

17:08.944 --> 17:11.823
There are a number of houses
opposite and along.

17:11.824 --> 17:16.502
Jubilee Terrace, numbers 35 to 75
overlook the site to some degree.

