34:29.264 --> 34:31.103
He said summat today. Odd.

34:31.103 --> 34:32.543
What?

34:32.543 --> 34:35.543
Miss Wealand,
this new one that reads with him.

34:35.543 --> 34:38.023
I've met her,
she seems right enough.

34:38.024 --> 34:40.463
He said they were talking
about things he likes

34:40.464 --> 34:41.862
and things he doesn't like.

34:41.864 --> 34:46.983
He doesn't like reading, for
instance, and he does like chips.

34:46.984 --> 34:51.143
And custard and football,
that kind of thing.

34:51.143 --> 34:55.703
Anyway, apparently, she said,
"What about your dad?

34:55.704 --> 34:57.303
"Do you like your dad?"

34:57.304 --> 35:00.703
And he says... He just said,
"We don't talk about me dad,"

35:00.704 --> 35:03.903
and that were it. But why's
she asking him about his dad?

35:03.904 --> 35:06.463
Doesn't she know not to do that?
Haven't they told her?

35:06.464 --> 35:08.503
Ask her next time you see her.

35:08.504 --> 35:10.503
She won't be back there now
till next Monday,

35:10.504 --> 35:12.904
she only works
Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday.

35:44.464 --> 35:46.223
Can you two brush your teeth?

35:46.224 --> 35:47.944
Now. Right now.

35:52.304 --> 35:55.143
And I know for a fact
you weren't out on obs that night,

35:55.144 --> 35:56.343
cos I rang Clifford.

35:56.344 --> 35:58.783
Pack your shit and move out,
that's all I've got to say.

35:58.784 --> 36:00.103
I'll just keep repeating it.

36:00.104 --> 36:02.463
For years, I've put up with you
coming in at all hours.

36:02.464 --> 36:05.023
I can't believe you're still here,
to be honest with you.

36:05.024 --> 36:07.383
You need to be the one
that moves out, John, not me.

36:07.384 --> 36:10.023
You neglected us. There's no wonder
things've happened.

36:10.024 --> 36:13.063
These kids don't know who you are.
Whore. Slapper.

36:13.064 --> 36:14.703
They prefer Graham to you. Slag.

36:14.704 --> 36:17.063
He helps 'em with their homework.
Trollop.

36:17.064 --> 36:19.063
He talks to them. Filthy bitch.

36:19.064 --> 36:20.623
Pox merchant.

36:20.624 --> 36:22.303
You weren't on obs. You're a liar.

36:22.304 --> 36:24.143
Oh, really?
And what would Clifford know?

36:24.144 --> 36:26.263
He never gets sent on obs
because of his sciatica.

36:26.264 --> 36:27.823
Yeah, maybe I'll ask Andy Shepherd.

36:27.824 --> 36:30.063
Yeah, you've got a hotline
to the superintendent.

36:30.064 --> 36:34.063
Yeah, well, maybe I have.
Yeah? Really? D'you want his number?

36:34.064 --> 36:36.503
Mr Tekeli, I read your statement
for that assault.

36:36.504 --> 36:37.863
I see we're still struggling

36:37.864 --> 36:39.903
with the I before E
except after C concept

36:39.904 --> 36:42.143
and can you find someone
with more time and patience

36:42.144 --> 36:44.703
than I have to explain to you
the difference when you spell

36:44.704 --> 36:48.823
"he threatened to break my arm"
and "I applied the foot brake"?

36:48.824 --> 36:50.544
Thank you.

36:52.224 --> 36:53.824
I got you this.

36:55.504 --> 36:59.783
To say sorry. I was, you know,
tired and emotional

36:59.784 --> 37:02.983
and out of order and I'm sorry.

37:02.984 --> 37:05.303
I thought it'd remind you of me,
cos it's prickly.

37:05.304 --> 37:07.783
And I'm prickly. In fact,
you could call it Catherine

37:07.784 --> 37:10.303
and then next time you get cross
with me, you could...

37:10.304 --> 37:14.303
Throw it at you.
Yeah. Er, yeah, that'd work.

37:14.304 --> 37:16.583
Or I could call it
by your nickname.

37:16.584 --> 37:18.303
That might make me happy.

37:18.304 --> 37:20.903
Sure! Absolutely.
Except I haven't got one.

37:20.904 --> 37:22.143
Oh, you do!

37:22.144 --> 37:23.584
No...

37:25.424 --> 37:27.983
Do I? Obviously not one
we use to your face.

37:27.984 --> 37:30.423
What is it?
Well, it's a secret from you.

37:30.424 --> 37:32.343
Obviously, everybody else knows it.

37:32.344 --> 37:35.263
Everybody upstairs
and up at headquarters

37:35.264 --> 37:37.583
and that lot down at t'cafe
that does us butties.

37:37.584 --> 37:39.623
Well, what is it, then? It's...

37:39.624 --> 37:41.903
It's... It's not very flattering.

37:41.904 --> 37:43.143
I haven't got a nickname.

37:43.144 --> 37:45.183
No. Good. OK.

37:45.184 --> 37:46.543
What is it, then?

37:46.544 --> 37:48.023
I accept your apology.

37:48.024 --> 37:50.303
What's my nickname?
You haven't got one.

37:50.304 --> 37:52.663
How long have I had it?
I shouldn't have said anything.

37:52.664 --> 37:55.103
What are you going to call
the cactus, then? Nothing.

37:55.104 --> 37:56.863
No, come on, tell me
or I'm taking it back.

37:56.864 --> 37:59.383
OK. No, tell me.

37:59.384 --> 38:01.103
Look, I didn't invent it.

38:01.104 --> 38:02.503
What is it?

38:02.504 --> 38:04.143
Come here.

38:04.144 --> 38:07.703
I'm not telling you.
Right, whatever.

38:07.704 --> 38:09.424
Keep the cactus. Mm.

38:11.784 --> 38:14.383
These are those dates when I was out
murdering prostitutes,

38:14.384 --> 38:16.303
if you still want
to check your diary.

38:16.304 --> 38:18.703
Nothing I'd rather do.
Come on, what is it?

38:18.704 --> 38:20.623
You used to be a detective.
Find out.

38:20.624 --> 38:22.383
I will. Good! Good luck.

38:22.384 --> 38:23.984
Right! Mm.

38:25.984 --> 38:27.143
Are you lying?

38:27.144 --> 38:29.663
'Bravo November 45.

38:29.664 --> 38:32.903
'Could you look at log 134 of today,
at Crow Wood Park?

38:32.904 --> 38:35.744
'We've had a phone call from a nun
about a suspected suicide.'

38:36.864 --> 38:40.743
A nun? 'Paramedics are on their way.
Can you get someone round there?'

38:40.744 --> 38:43.423
A real nun? No, a pretend one(!)

38:43.424 --> 38:44.583
Responding.

38:44.584 --> 38:47.103
They might be dressed up
going to a hen party.

38:47.104 --> 38:49.783
Ten o'clock in t'morning?
Charlie Oscar 965.

38:49.784 --> 38:51.864
They might still be out
from the night before.

38:53.504 --> 38:55.303
Charlie Oscar 965.

38:55.304 --> 38:57.143
It's baptism of fire time, kid.

38:57.144 --> 38:58.943
We've got a suicide
up Crow Wood Park.

38:58.944 --> 39:02.023
'I'm coming to pick you up,
you're coming wi' me.'

39:02.024 --> 39:04.463
"We don't talk about me dad?"

39:04.464 --> 39:07.223
Yeah. But, listen, don't get cross!

39:07.224 --> 39:10.303
He said that, but then nothing
could be further from the truth.

39:10.304 --> 39:14.064
Once he started, it was like
he could talk about nothing else.

39:15.464 --> 39:16.703
What did he say?

39:16.704 --> 39:18.623
He said how much he liked you

39:18.624 --> 39:21.943
when he met you outside the shop
and on the boat

39:21.944 --> 39:24.223
and how he still thinks about you.

39:24.224 --> 39:26.583
Did he say that?
Did he actually say that?

39:26.584 --> 39:28.823
That he still thinks about me?
Every day.

39:28.824 --> 39:30.544
Yes. He said it.

39:32.144 --> 39:34.263
Yeah, but in a bad way.

39:34.264 --> 39:37.303
No!
He talked about bringing you milk.

39:37.304 --> 39:40.063
And how he upset you
by bringing his friend

39:40.064 --> 39:42.943
and how much he wishes
he hadn't done that now

39:42.944 --> 39:45.744
because that seemed
to spoil everything.

39:47.704 --> 39:49.264
Did he...?

39:51.384 --> 39:54.783
Did he say owt about me
chucking petrol all over him?

39:54.784 --> 39:56.583
He did. Yeah.

39:56.584 --> 39:58.223
That was really interesting,

39:58.224 --> 40:00.983
because he says
that all he can think of now

40:00.984 --> 40:03.783
is how ill you were when that
happened. I was.

40:03.784 --> 40:07.263
I WAS. I had septicaemia.
I were off me head, I nearly died!

40:07.264 --> 40:08.983
He thinks it's his fault. Eh?

40:08.984 --> 40:11.423
He said if he hadn't
brought his friend,

40:11.424 --> 40:13.984
you wouldn't have got upset
that day and done that.

40:15.104 --> 40:18.784
It wasn't his friend, as such.
He were a nice enough little lad.

40:20.064 --> 40:23.583
I were just frightened they were
going to tell people where I was,

40:23.584 --> 40:25.743
cos I knew they'd crucify me.

40:25.744 --> 40:28.143
I would never have hurt him,
Frances.

40:28.144 --> 40:29.864
Never.

40:31.784 --> 40:34.063
Not in a million years.

40:34.064 --> 40:36.224
I were just off me head.

40:38.024 --> 40:40.943
You see, I think he knows that.
Did he say it?

40:40.944 --> 40:43.463
No, no, but I could see in his eyes

40:43.464 --> 40:46.143
that he still really
thinks about you.

40:46.144 --> 40:48.144
In a good way.

40:49.984 --> 40:51.024
Hm!

40:52.984 --> 40:55.584
"We don't talk about me dad"!

40:58.264 --> 41:01.383
You see, she'll be trying to fill
his head with shit about me.

41:01.384 --> 41:03.903
You've got to tell him stuff,
Frances.

41:03.904 --> 41:06.303
You have got to make sure
he knows stuff.

41:06.304 --> 41:09.023
If you don't, nobody else will.
I can't. I will.

41:09.024 --> 41:10.903
Obviously, I will eventually...

41:10.904 --> 41:14.183
And all the other stuff,
all the lies I got convicted over.

41:14.184 --> 41:17.063
I did not rape Ann Gallagher.
That were Lewis.

41:17.064 --> 41:19.863
It were me that used to bring her
Mars bars and let her use t'bucket.

41:19.864 --> 41:23.023
I did not kill that little
police girl up on t'moor either.

41:23.024 --> 41:24.183
That were Lewis.

41:24.184 --> 41:28.383
And I had to kill him, cos he come at me with
that knife! I know. But nobody believes me.

41:28.384 --> 41:29.704
I do.

41:31.184 --> 41:32.304
Yeah.

41:33.824 --> 41:35.784
Except you.

41:44.224 --> 41:47.063
I did kick the shite
out of his granny,

41:47.064 --> 41:49.903
but A, she were asking for it,

41:49.904 --> 41:52.463
and B, she would have killed me.

41:52.464 --> 41:54.543
Spraying me wi' that stuff!

41:54.544 --> 41:57.503
She would have killed me
on that boat an' all

41:57.504 --> 41:59.543
if that woman hadn't come
and pulled her off me,

41:59.544 --> 42:02.183
and has she ever
been taken to court over that?

42:02.184 --> 42:03.943
Has she hell as like!

42:03.944 --> 42:07.143
And now there's been another murder
on t'news. Have you seen it?

42:07.144 --> 42:09.064
Yeah. Just the same as me mother.

42:10.424 --> 42:12.744
She is a clever bitch...

42:14.184 --> 42:16.584
...making it look like
a serial killer.

42:18.384 --> 42:19.983
You see, I know.

42:19.984 --> 42:23.223
I've told you before,
I know how a bitch like that thinks.

42:23.224 --> 42:25.264
She is poison, her.

42:27.784 --> 42:29.744
She's dangerous.

42:33.824 --> 42:37.664
I know we try not to have
nasty thoughts, Frances, but...

42:41.784 --> 42:44.824
...she needs putting out of
her misery, that one.

42:52.504 --> 42:55.983
He's been talking about things
at home.

42:55.984 --> 42:58.063
His Auntie Clare drinks.

42:58.064 --> 43:00.263
I've met her. She's a nice woman.

43:00.264 --> 43:03.863
But between the grandmother's anger
and his auntie's problem,

43:03.864 --> 43:06.063
yes, we could ask for better things.

43:06.064 --> 43:08.023
We have to get him out of there.

43:08.024 --> 43:10.663
Well, we can't get him
out of there just yet.

43:10.664 --> 43:13.984
But we can keep an eye on him.
Can't we? No...

43:15.304 --> 43:18.063
Frances, I keep telling you...

43:18.064 --> 43:20.504
and you keep not hearing me!

43:25.704 --> 43:28.024
That is not enough.

43:34.024 --> 43:39.343
If a detective - he's a sergeant -
asks me out for a drink,

43:39.344 --> 43:41.584
that's not unethical, is it?

43:43.904 --> 43:45.983
Is he married?

43:45.984 --> 43:48.863
Well, yeah, he is,
but he's just found out

43:48.864 --> 43:51.903
his wife's been having it off
with someone else, so...

43:51.904 --> 43:53.863
Is he old enough to be your dad?

43:53.864 --> 43:55.103
No.

43:55.104 --> 43:57.023
Yeah, actually. He probably is.

43:57.024 --> 44:01.023
He's not as old as my dad,
but, yeah, technically.

44:01.024 --> 44:03.663
And do you believe him
about his wife?

44:03.664 --> 44:06.943
I don't fancy him. We're just mates.

44:06.944 --> 44:09.143
Yeah, but is that what he thinks?

44:09.144 --> 44:11.863
It's not really ethics, is it, love?

44:11.864 --> 44:14.544
It's about whether it's wise or not.

44:23.384 --> 44:24.863
You know at work...

44:24.864 --> 44:26.623
Yeah?

44:26.624 --> 44:29.063
Have I got a nickname?

44:29.064 --> 44:30.784
One or two.

44:36.424 --> 44:38.063
One or two?

44:38.064 --> 44:39.744
I don't use them.

44:42.064 --> 44:44.663
Oh... That bad, eh?

44:44.664 --> 44:47.583
Do you think maybe
I COULD go for a drink with him?

44:47.584 --> 44:49.903
See, I'm interested
in the possibility

44:49.904 --> 44:52.183
of becoming a detective,
eventually, so..

44:52.184 --> 44:54.543
So what are they, then,
these nicknames?

44:54.544 --> 44:57.343
Why are you putting me on the spot?
Cos you're here.

44:57.344 --> 44:58.743
I've never met a nun.

44:58.744 --> 45:00.983
The way you changed
the subject then

45:00.984 --> 45:02.903
was so subtle, I barely noticed(!)

45:02.904 --> 45:05.743
Me dad says it's a compliment
when people have a nickname.

45:05.744 --> 45:07.943
He says people don't bother
giving a nickname

45:07.944 --> 45:09.743
to someone
they're not bothered about.

45:09.744 --> 45:12.783
So, well, what are they, then?
I wouldn't worry about it.

45:12.784 --> 45:14.663
I'm not worried.

45:14.664 --> 45:16.103
I'm delighted.

45:16.104 --> 45:19.743
I didn't know I had a nickname.
Two nicknames.

45:19.744 --> 45:22.823
Hello. Are you all right, love?

45:22.824 --> 45:25.703
Just a bit of shock.
She's going to be absolutely fine.

45:25.704 --> 45:27.504
Right. So where is it?

45:29.304 --> 45:31.183
Who found him? You?

45:31.184 --> 45:32.983
Yes, it was us that phoned.

45:32.984 --> 45:37.183
Vodka bottles everywhere.
He must've got tanked up to do it.

45:37.184 --> 45:38.543
OK.

45:38.544 --> 45:41.463
Can you get a first account
out of those two for me?

45:41.464 --> 45:44.223
Who they are, what they're doing
here, where they're from.

45:44.224 --> 45:47.103
They're nuns, I shouldn't think
they're up to much. He's dead.

45:47.104 --> 45:48.863
Thanks, love. It's on the left.

45:48.864 --> 45:51.383
Careful as you go down.
It's a bit slippery.

45:51.384 --> 45:53.543
They'll be from St Werburgh's.

45:53.544 --> 45:56.583
Find out if they walk through here
regularly and, if they do,

45:56.584 --> 45:58.103
at what times,

45:58.104 --> 46:01.343
and if they're familiar with anybody
else who walks through here.

46:01.344 --> 46:03.783
Bravo November 45,
I'm in Crow Wood Park,

46:03.784 --> 46:06.623
suspected suicide confirmed dead
by the paramedic.

46:06.624 --> 46:08.063
We need a CSI here

46:08.064 --> 46:11.024
and somebody from CID,
if there's anyone available.

46:19.144 --> 46:21.183
Wow...

46:21.184 --> 46:22.543
Yeah.

46:22.544 --> 46:25.423
How are you going to get him down?
That's easy.

46:25.424 --> 46:28.463
I'm going to wait for CID to turn up
and let them do it.

46:28.464 --> 46:31.343
So, come on. These names.

46:31.344 --> 46:33.823
Just spit 'em out quickly,
then it's done with.

46:33.824 --> 46:36.503
I don't want to be, like,
the messenger that gets shot.

46:36.504 --> 46:38.863
What, do you think
I'm that small-minded?

46:38.864 --> 46:40.903
Shall I go
and take those first accounts?

46:40.904 --> 46:44.343
I'll tell you what... You can
write 'em down, if it's easier.

46:44.344 --> 46:47.343
I'm not sure I should.
No, love, I'm not asking you.

46:47.344 --> 46:49.663
I think, going back to ethics,

46:49.664 --> 46:52.703
you shouldn't use your rank to make
me tell you something like that.

46:52.704 --> 46:54.343
Rank? We're friends.

46:54.344 --> 46:56.183
Not at work! You said that.

46:56.184 --> 46:58.783
I saved your life from that bastard.

46:58.784 --> 47:02.223
Yeah, go on, lady.
Get round that one.

47:02.224 --> 47:04.904
Do you really want to know
that badly?

47:06.384 --> 47:07.904
Catherine?

47:09.984 --> 47:11.543
Are they really shit?

47:11.544 --> 47:13.104
No.

47:14.784 --> 47:17.223
They're affectionate but, you know,

47:17.224 --> 47:21.184
not... not... not something you might
choose for yourself. That's all.

47:22.704 --> 47:25.344
If you really want to know,
I WILL tell you.

47:27.824 --> 47:29.344
What's up?

47:30.424 --> 47:31.863
I know him.

47:31.864 --> 47:34.223
It's that bloke I tasered.

47:34.224 --> 47:37.104
They let him out on bail yesterday.

47:41.304 --> 47:43.304
Do you want to do the talking?

47:45.264 --> 47:46.863
Good practice for you.

47:46.864 --> 47:49.423
And anyway, look,
it was me that tasered him.

47:49.424 --> 47:51.863
If we weren't so understaffed
and under-resourced,

47:51.864 --> 47:53.663
I wouldn't even be here.

47:53.664 --> 47:55.864
This is bordering on awkward.

48:05.424 --> 48:07.503
Mrs Dragovic? There's no-one here.

48:07.504 --> 48:09.223
Is your husband Goran Dragovic?

48:09.224 --> 48:11.983
He's not here, he works shifts.
Could we come in?

48:11.984 --> 48:15.703
It's not a good time for me,
I'm busy, I'm going out.

48:15.704 --> 48:19.263
It's important, Mrs Dragovic.
There's been an accident.

48:19.264 --> 48:22.424
What accident? Can we...?

48:29.064 --> 48:31.384
You might want to sit down.

48:38.704 --> 48:41.303
Hiya. Oh, hello.

48:41.304 --> 48:44.383
I saw a dead body this morning.
This fella hanged himself.

48:44.384 --> 48:46.063
You'll get used to it.

48:46.064 --> 48:48.463
I didn't mind. I was fascinated.

48:48.464 --> 48:50.063
His tongue was like...

48:50.064 --> 48:52.143
and his lips were blue, proper blue,

48:52.144 --> 48:55.223
and his eyes were all,
like, bulging out.

48:55.224 --> 48:58.023
Does that make me weird?
Not being freaked?

48:58.024 --> 49:01.423
Is it true that men get an erection
when they hang?

49:01.424 --> 49:04.783
Well, it depends what
they were doing at the time.

49:04.784 --> 49:07.303
So normally not, then?

49:07.304 --> 49:09.183
Nah. It's a myth.

49:09.184 --> 49:12.623
OK. Good! Well, there you go.
I've learned something!

49:12.624 --> 49:15.583
Inspector Taylor sent me up
with this for Mr Shepherd.

49:15.584 --> 49:17.823
Is he in? No, he's stepped out.

49:17.824 --> 49:20.503
It's nothing. It's just
Brunhilde's alibi. Finally.

49:20.504 --> 49:23.183
Joyce at t'front desk
worked it out. Brunhilde?

49:23.184 --> 49:25.503
Miss Trunchbull. Sergeant Cawood.

49:25.504 --> 49:27.824
I'll put it on his desk.

49:29.504 --> 49:31.464
You still want to go for a drink?

49:33.504 --> 49:35.943
Well, yeah. Yeah, if you...
I would!

49:35.944 --> 49:37.223
Tonight? Moorings?

49:37.224 --> 49:39.544
Seven? Half past? Great. Seven.

49:43.664 --> 49:45.943
Where's all the boards?

49:45.944 --> 49:47.543
What boards?

49:47.544 --> 49:49.623
You know, on telly,
they have all glass boards

49:49.624 --> 49:52.943
with photos of the deceased
and clues and, you know, stuff.

49:52.944 --> 49:55.663
Yeah, well,
in real life, we have these.

49:55.664 --> 49:57.623
Can I look? Er...

49:57.624 --> 50:01.183
No. It's... There's some
pretty graphic stuff in there.

50:01.184 --> 50:03.064
I want to be a detective.

50:04.384 --> 50:06.423
I want to do what you lot do.

50:06.424 --> 50:08.183
Ma'am?

50:08.184 --> 50:09.704
Sure!

50:19.304 --> 50:21.623
Is this the most recent victim?

50:21.624 --> 50:22.904
Yeah.

50:25.064 --> 50:28.183
How was the postmortem?
Did you learn anything?

50:28.184 --> 50:29.783
Oh, just...

50:29.784 --> 50:31.343
Not much.

50:31.344 --> 50:33.183
Well, nothing relevant.

50:33.184 --> 50:35.383
Well, we think
she's not a prostitute, John.

50:35.384 --> 50:37.023
That's pretty relevant. Not?

50:37.024 --> 50:39.463
Oh, yeah, yeah. The clothes.

50:39.464 --> 50:43.183
Expensive dress and shoes,
other lifestyle...

50:43.184 --> 50:46.383
You know, she didn't smoke,
didn't drink, she...

50:46.384 --> 50:48.943
Her teeth were well looked after.
So, yeah, yeah.

50:48.944 --> 50:51.583
So... how will you identify her?

50:51.584 --> 50:55.703
Well, sometimes we get
a DNA match on our database,

50:55.704 --> 50:59.823
but that's usually only if they've
committed a crime in the past.

50:59.824 --> 51:03.383
And she hasn't, so we've been
looking at missing persons, but...

51:03.384 --> 51:05.263
You know we never found the woman

51:05.264 --> 51:08.743
who lived in the burnt-out flat
in Ripponden, don't you?

51:08.744 --> 51:10.543
Two weeks ago.

51:10.544 --> 51:12.503
Yeah, no, as I say, you know,

51:12.504 --> 51:14.983
we've, er... we've checked
all the local mispers,

51:14.984 --> 51:17.343
but she's probably been cleared
for whatever reason.

51:17.344 --> 51:19.263
No, this woman isn't a misper.

51:19.264 --> 51:21.663
No-one ever actually
reported her missing, as such.

51:21.664 --> 51:24.063
She's called Victoria Fleming,
Vicky Fleming,

51:24.064 --> 51:26.303
and how old is your woman?

51:26.304 --> 51:28.143
Between 45 and 55.

51:28.144 --> 51:31.184
That's... That would fit the bill.
Really?

51:32.904 --> 51:35.263
This is her? Yeah.

51:35.264 --> 51:38.303
Blonde shoulder-length hair,
slim build.

51:38.304 --> 51:40.543
I've got a photo of her on file.

51:40.544 --> 51:42.063
Me and Shaf went down to talk to HR

51:42.064 --> 51:44.263
at the department store
where she works.

51:44.264 --> 51:46.583
We made a copy.
Shall I e-mail it to you?

51:46.584 --> 51:50.984
Well, that's... that's... That'd be
really helpful, if you could. Right.

51:53.624 --> 51:56.704
Hm. Joined-up thinking.

51:58.384 --> 52:00.264
Why didn't we know about this?

52:02.944 --> 52:04.903
'You're kidding.' Nope.

52:04.904 --> 52:08.343
Well done. Fantastic!
Thank you, Joyce. Thank you.

52:08.344 --> 52:10.464
Yeah, well,
that's what friends are...

52:15.704 --> 52:17.943
The night Aurelia Petrovic
was murdered,

52:17.944 --> 52:21.303
this is five months ago,
I was at Oldham Coliseum with Joyce

52:21.304 --> 52:23.623
dressed up like a pillock
for the Rocky Horror Show!

52:23.624 --> 52:26.583
She invited me at the last second
cos her cousin dropped out.

52:26.584 --> 52:28.503
That's why it never went
on me calendar.

52:28.504 --> 52:30.583
So when Aurelia Petrovic
was getting slashed,

52:30.584 --> 52:33.503
you and Joyce were doing
the Time Warp. Isn't life weird?

52:33.504 --> 52:37.143
I can't picture that.
Yeah, don't try.

52:37.144 --> 52:40.263
Off the hook. It's official.

52:40.264 --> 52:42.343
Not the guilty party after all.

52:42.344 --> 52:45.183
So Jodie Shackleton can stick that
up her pipe and smoke it.

52:45.184 --> 52:47.223
IN her pipe and smoke it.

52:47.224 --> 52:50.223
I don't care where she sticks it.
I've rung her anyway.

52:50.224 --> 52:52.143
I've told her. (Bitch.)

52:52.144 --> 52:54.303
Neil's coming for his tea. OK.

52:54.304 --> 52:56.423
You won't frighten him, will you?

52:56.424 --> 52:58.023
I will do me best.

52:58.024 --> 53:00.784
And can you ask Daniel not to be...
weird with him?

53:03.024 --> 53:04.464
Sure.

53:06.304 --> 53:08.583
How was school? Boring.

53:08.584 --> 53:12.983
Oi, what's this about Miss Wealand
asking you about your dad?

53:12.984 --> 53:16.543
Nothing. I told her, I said,
"We don't talk about me dad."

53:16.544 --> 53:20.263
What have I told you about kicking
your ball against Winnie's wall?

53:20.264 --> 53:21.944
Well, keep it that way.

53:27.424 --> 53:30.144
It's only me. All right?

53:32.144 --> 53:33.783
I've got good news.

53:33.784 --> 53:35.703
Well, it's macabre news.

53:35.704 --> 53:37.864
Goran Dragovic is dead.

53:39.984 --> 53:43.104
Suicide. He hanged himself
from a tree in Crow Wood Park.

53:55.264 --> 53:58.903
She... She says he would never
kill himself. It's them.

53:58.904 --> 54:02.144
They shut him up
so he won't... he won't talk.

54:24.144 --> 54:25.343
Hello.

54:25.344 --> 54:27.943
Bloody hell, John,
it's definitely Vicky Fleming.

54:27.944 --> 54:32.823
I've spoken to the OIC on District and I've
given the lab a bell to chassey them along

54:32.824 --> 54:35.823
for any DNA matches they might
have found from the personal stuff

54:35.824 --> 54:37.623
they got from her workplace, but...

54:37.624 --> 54:41.543
Oh, it's her. I mean, you can see
it's her from the photos.

54:41.544 --> 54:43.423
She's even, in one of these photos,

54:43.424 --> 54:46.184
wearing that same dress
she was wearing when she died.

54:47.944 --> 54:49.743
'John?'

54:49.744 --> 54:51.463
Great.

54:51.464 --> 54:52.823
Yeah.

54:52.824 --> 54:55.744
Have you told the boss? Yeah.

54:57.744 --> 55:00.543
Well done.
'Right. I'll see you, then.'

55:00.544 --> 55:02.064
Bye.

55:23.464 --> 55:25.343
Are you all right, love?

55:25.344 --> 55:27.503
I'm fine, I'm fine, I'm sorry.

55:27.504 --> 55:31.343
You were right over the wrong side
of the road. I'm sorry.

55:31.344 --> 55:32.823
Are you OK?

55:32.824 --> 55:34.863
Yeah. Um...

55:34.864 --> 55:37.104
I'm just a bit shaken.

55:38.504 --> 55:40.903
Are you all right?
Yeah, I'm fine, love.

55:40.904 --> 55:43.663
You just gave me
a bit of a surprise, that's all.

55:43.664 --> 55:46.384
You want to be more careful.

56:32.344 --> 56:34.863
♪ In this trouble town

56:34.864 --> 56:38.184
♪ Troubles are found

56:40.584 --> 56:43.343
♪ In this trouble town

56:43.344 --> 56:46.584
♪ Word soon gets round

56:52.984 --> 56:56.823
♪ Stuck in speed bump city
Where the only thing that's pretty

56:56.824 --> 56:59.344
♪ Is the thought of getting out. ♪

